    ## Create a task

    ```
    POST /tasks.json
    ```

    ### Example

    ```bash
    $ curl  -H 'X-TODO-Token: <username>:<api_key>' \
            -X POST \
            -d '<json>' \
            http://todo.herokuapp.com/tasks.json
    ```

    ### Response

    ```json
    {
      "id": 40,
      "user_id": 1,
      "content": "Watch Game of Thrones",
      "priority": 3,
      "due_date": "2013-10-26",
      "complete": false,
      "created_at": "2013-10-20T22:13:07.102Z",
      "updated_at": "2013-10-21T21:26:00.108Z"
    }
    ```

    ## Update a task

    ```
    PATCH /tasks/:id.json
    ```

    ### Example

    ```bash
    $ curl  -H 'X-TODO-Token: <username>:<api_key>' \
            -X PATCH \
            -d '<json>' \
            http://todo.herokuapp.com/tasks/40.json
    ```

    ### Response

    Responds with `200` if everything went well.

    ## Delete a task

    ```
    DELETE /tasks/:id.json
    ```

    ### Example

    ```bash
    $ curl  -H 'X-TODO-Token: <username>:<api_key>' \
            -X DELETE \
            http://todo.herokuapp.com/tasks/40.json
    ```

    ### Response

    Responds with `200` if everything went well.
